Participation in the activities of an organisation, related with the students' field of specialisation, during a minimum period of 220 hours. Collection and analysis of information. General overview. Organisational structure and processes. Customers. Services. Micro environment and macro environment. Sustainability. Benchmarking the organisation. SWOT analysis. Proposals for redevelopment. Self-examination. Preparation of the internship report.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The general objective is to support the convergence of theory and practice, encouraging students to learn from practice and put the acquired knowledge into practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students are expected to achieve the following outcomes upon completion of the subject. Students will know and understand: *	current problems in organisations providing wellness-oriented services;  and acquire skills: *	to analyse the environment, organisational structure and processes; *	to benchmark organisations and design redevelopment; *	to manage the activities of the organization.
